  "text": "Our final experiment is to identify the class labels on three real time series datasets: ECG, Wafer and Gun Point [CITATION_1] . The ECG dataset is a time series of the measurements recorded by one electrode during one heartbeat. The data has been annotated by cardiologists and a label of normal or abnormal is assigned to each data record. The Gun Point dataset contains two-dimensional time series extracted from video of two actors either aiming a gun or simply pointing at a target. The two dimensions correspond to the X and Y coordinates of the actors right hand, we only discuss the Y-Axes as X-Axes is not available. The Wafer dataset is recorded by one vacuumchamber sensor during the etch process of silicon wafers for semiconductor fabrication with the normal or abnormal.",
